    "Name": "Coriolis CRLS-286",
    "Details": "The CRLS-286 is an early 26th century assault mech that remains dangerous despite its age. An AC/20 and AC/10 give it devastating close-range ballistic output, backed by Medium and Small Lasers for additional bite. Three jump jets on a 90-ton frame make it genuinely surprising in close quarters, letting pilots vault into rear arcs where the combined autocannon volley can wreck even well-armored opponents in a single pass.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Accurate Weapon - AC</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.14</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limit: Right Lower</color>",
